{
  "stem": "12289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, not-- not more than-- than they marched in with their tanks and the-- their army.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the-- the people of Budapest were standing around and looking at this, quite horrified.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there was no one-- no fighting.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was nothing of that kind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because Hungary was, after all, an ally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was kind of a peace-- so to say, peaceful occupation of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, at the same time, the-- the Germans were clever enough to-- to leave the-- the-- the-- the sort of administration and the government in-- in the Hungarian hands.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they-- they saw to it, of course, that there was a German, pro-German government at that time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the war was the-- the-- the Hungarian ambassador to Berlin-- Sztojay was his name, he became the first prime minister in this pro-German government-- in-- and-- shortly after the arrival of the Germans, then, in-- in March, April.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were not typically-- they were not really Nazi people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were pro-Germans.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and the-- and the Germans were satisfied to have them and gave them, sort of, carte blanche to-- they could act as they wanted.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They want-- they were-- were eager to show that they respected the independence of Hungary, even if they were not independent, because the Germans were always behind.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But, sort of, officially, they-- they were-- their-- their affairs were in their own hands, so-- so to say.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all this, this long period-- not long.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was from-- from when the-- the arrival of the Germans till-- till the fall, till-- it was August, September, or something like that, when we managed to get on very good speaking terms with this government.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- because the Germans didn't interfere, so we could make all these agreements with them.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
